page.title: 04A FAVOURITE WALK
page.content: THIS WALK WAS WALKED IN JUNE.THE PLACE WALKED WAS JUST NORTH OF SALINE. FROM THE ROAD MANY FIELDS CAN BE SEEN,THE FIELDS CONTAIN GRASS FOR SHEEP AND CATTLE. A FEW FARM HOUSES LINE THE ROAD AND A SPRING FLOWS BETWEEN THEM. THE VALLEY IS 'U' SHAPED AND THE HILLS ARE UNDULATED.THE SPRING SEEN EARLIER RUNS THROUGH HERE AS A MISFIT STREAM. THERE ARE A FEW TREES,WIND BRAKES,AND MANY RABITS CAN BE SEEN EVEN A FOX CARRYING ITS PREY. A DENSELY WOODED STREAM RUNS UNDER THE ROAD,MANY BIRDS CAN BE SEEN AND HEARD WITHIN THESE TREES.
